#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:3
msgid "Using F2PY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:5
msgid ""
"This page contains a reference to all command-line options for the ``f2py`` "
"command, as well as a reference to internal functions of the ``numpy.f2py`` "
"module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:10
msgid "Using ``f2py`` as a command-line tool"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:12
msgid ""
"When used as a command-line tool, ``f2py`` has three major modes, "
"distinguished by the usage of ``-c`` and ``-h`` switches."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:16
msgid "1. Signature file generation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:18
msgid "To scan Fortran sources and generate a signature file, use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:20
msgid ""
"f2py -h <filename.pyf> <options> <fortran files>   \\\n"
"  [[ only: <fortran functions>  : ]                \\\n"
"    [ skip: <fortran functions>  : ]]...           \\\n"
"  [<fortran files> ...]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:29
msgid ""
"A Fortran source file can contain many routines, and it is often not "
"necessary to allow all routines to be usable from Python. In such cases, "
"either specify which routines should be wrapped (in the ``only: .. :`` part) "
"or which routines F2PY should ignore (in the ``skip: .. :`` part)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:34
msgid ""
"F2PY has no concept of a \"per-file\" ``skip`` or ``only`` list, so if "
"functions are listed in ``only``, no other functions will be taken from any "
"other files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:37
msgid ""
"If ``<filename.pyf>`` is specified as ``stdout``, then signatures are "
"written to standard output instead of a file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:40
msgid ""
"Among other options (see below), the following can be used in this mode:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:43
msgid "``--overwrite-signature``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:43
msgid "Overwrites an existing signature file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:46
msgid "2. Extension module construction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:48
msgid "To construct an extension module, use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:50
msgid ""
"f2py -m <modulename> <options> <fortran files>   \\\n"
"  [[ only: <fortran functions>  : ]              \\\n"
"    [ skip: <fortran functions>  : ]]...          \\\n"
"  [<fortran files> ...]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:57
msgid ""
"The constructed extension module is saved as ``<modulename>module.c`` to the "
"current directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:60
msgid ""
"Here ``<fortran files>`` may also contain signature files. Among other "
"options (see below), the following options can be used in this mode:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:66
msgid "``--debug-capi``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:64
msgid ""
"Adds debugging hooks to the extension module. When using this extension "
"module, various diagnostic information about the wrapper is written to the "
"standard output, for example, the values of variables, the steps taken, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:82
msgid "``-include'<includefile>'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:69
msgid ""
"Add a CPP ``#include`` statement to the extension module source. "
"``<includefile>`` should be given in one of the following forms"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:72
msgid ""
"\"filename.ext\"\n"
"<filename.ext>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:77
msgid ""
"The include statement is inserted just before the wrapper functions. This "
"feature enables using arbitrary C functions (defined in ``<includefile>``) "
"in F2PY generated wrappers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:81
msgid ""
"This option is deprecated. Use ``usercode`` statement to specify C code "
"snippets directly in signature files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:87
msgid "``--[no-]wrap-functions``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:85
msgid ""
"Create Fortran subroutine wrappers to Fortran functions. ``--wrap-"
"functions`` is default because it ensures maximum portability and compiler "
"independence."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:94
msgid "``--[no-]freethreading-compatible``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:90
msgid ""
"Create a module that declares it does or doesn't require the GIL. The "
"default is ``--no-freethreading-compatible`` for backwards compatibility. "
"Inspect the fortran code you are wrapping for thread safety issues before "
"passing ``--freethreading-compatible``, as ``f2py`` does not analyze fortran "
"code for thread safety issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:102
msgid "``--include-paths \"<path1>:<path2>...\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:97
msgid "Search include files from given directories."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:99
msgid ""
"The paths are to be separated by the correct operating system separator :py:"
"data:`~os.pathsep`, that is ``:`` on Linux / MacOS and ``;`` on Windows. In "
"``CMake`` this corresponds to using ``$<SEMICOLON>``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:105
msgid "3. Building a module"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:107
msgid "To build an extension module, use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:109
msgid ""
"f2py -c <options> <fortran files>       \\\n"
"  [[ only: <fortran functions>  : ]     \\\n"
"    [ skip: <fortran functions>  : ]]... \\\n"
"  [ <fortran/c source files> ] [ <.o, .a, .so files> ]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:116
msgid ""
"If ``<fortran files>`` contains a signature file, then the source for an "
"extension module is constructed, all Fortran and C sources are compiled, and "
"finally all object and library files are linked to the extension module "
"``<modulename>.so`` which is saved into the current directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:121
msgid ""
"If ``<fortran files>`` does not contain a signature file, then an extension "
"module is constructed by scanning all Fortran source codes for routine "
"signatures, before proceeding to build the extension module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:126
msgid ""
"``distutils`` has been removed. Use environment variables or native files to "
"interact with ``meson`` instead. See its `FAQ <https://mesonbuild.com/howtox."
"html>`__ for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:130
msgid ""
"Among other options (see below) and options described for previous modes, "
"the following can be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:134
msgid "The ``distutils`` backend has been removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:137
msgid "Common build flags:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:139
msgid "``--backend <backend_type>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:140
msgid "Legacy option, only ``meson`` is supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:141
msgid "``--f77flags=<string>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:142
msgid "Specify F77 compiler flags"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:143
msgid "``--f90flags=<string>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:144
msgid "Specify F90 compiler flags"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:145
msgid "``--debug``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:146
msgid "Compile with debugging information"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:147
msgid "``-l<libname>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:148
msgid "Use the library ``<libname>`` when linking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:149
msgid "``-D<macro>[=<defn=1>]``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:150
msgid "Define macro ``<macro>`` as ``<defn>``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:151
msgid "``-U<macro>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/usage.rst:152
